    "abstract": "<jats:title>ABSTRACT</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>SARS-CoV-2 infects the respiratory tract, lung and then other organs. However, its pathogenesis remains largely unknown. We used RareScope\u2122 Fluorescence Light Sheet Microscopy (FLSM) and fluorescent in situ hybridization of RNA (RNA-FISH) to detect SARS-CoV-2 RNA and dissemination kinetics in mouse blood circulation. By RNA-FISH, we found that SARS-CoV-2 RNA-positive leukocytes, including CD11c cells, appeared as early as one day after infection and continued through day 10 post infection. Our data suggest that SARS-CoV-2-permissive leukocytes contribute to systemic viral dissemination, and RNA-FISH combined with FLSM can be utilized as a sensitive tool for SARS-CoV-2 detection in blood specimens.</jats:p>",
